sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1973017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: nahR (Pseudomonas putida, see BBa_K1031610) is expressed under the constitutive Pr promoter. It encodes a regulatory protein that activates the Psal promoter (see BBa_J61051) in the presence of salicylate. nasF (see BBa_K1973001) is an attenuator of transcription elongation (terminator) from Klebsiella pneumoniae that decreases the basal expression from the Psal promoter. xylS2 (BBa_K1973002) codifies the modified XylS2 protein from Pseudomonas putida MT1, which is a transcriptional activator of the Pm promoter in response to salicylate. This module provides a tight expression regulation by salicylate thanks to a two-step (NahR and XylS2) system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alvaro Escobar Doncel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We digested BBa_K1973002 as a vector (EcoRI and XbaI) and BBa_K1973005 as an insert (EcoRI and SpeI), and then we ligate them.
